[Although we all applaud the humane acts of assisting the birthing animals,
the larger issue appears to be the continuing outbreak of the disease. The
second article indicates there is a a delay between diagnosis and
termination/incineration of the animals. Outbreaks will continue as long
there is this delay. During '67-'68 outbreak, we only turned the corner
when the majority of herds were killed THE SAME day as
diagnosis. If you wait, the herd/flock is still pumping out virus,
infecting others. This is very important. My thanks to Dr. Hugh-Jones for
his insight with this disease. - Mod.TG
